reviews.review_text: The Garden This place always seemed like it had a good vibe like the Oakland Coliseum. Excellent show minus the saxaphone. With some bands guest artists add to the show - with the Grateful Dead for some odd reason it always detracted the show. Same with opening acts etc. The Dead were best just as it was laid out in the sequences without interuptions.
